observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Supply Officer:

•   Renew PARs every three years and every time there is a change in 	custodianship;

•	Ensure that the end-user duly acknowledge receipt of properties by signing 	in the “Received from” portion and the Supply Officer sign the “issued by”  	portion of the PAR to pinpoint responsibility over the PPE;

•	Ensure that the PARs are properly numbered and dated in accordance with 	the numbering under Section 58 of GAM for LGUs, Volume II to serve as 	controlling measure and to determine when is the next renewal of PARs; 	and

•	Ensure that the ICS is use to issue tangible items which costs ₱15,000.00 	and below and has life of more than one year in accordance with Section 59 	of GAM for LGUs, Volume II.

We recommended that:

For future similar transactions, management ensure that these are supported with the documents as required under DSWD Memorandum Circular No. 24, series of 2020;

Management ensure that only the approved payrolls for which a cash advance is drawn are paid out of said cash advance; 


The disbursing officer refrain from revising the payrolls once approved for payment and, if there are eligible beneficiaries not included and funds are still available, prepare a supplemental payroll for approval by proper authorities; and

The disbursing officer ensure that acknowledgment of receipt of claim by each payee is clearly shown in the payroll and attach authorization letters of payees whose claims are received by their authorized representatives.

We recommended that management:

 a.	Cause the disposal of the unserviceable properties in accordance with the guidelines on disposal of property;



b.	Upon disposal of the properties, the Property and/or Supply Unit submit the Inventory and Inspection Report of Unserviceable Property (IIRUP) to the Accounting Unit, which will be the basis for the dropping of the  properties from the book of accounts and for taking up the proceeds from the sale of the property, if any.

We recommended that Management, thru the SWMB:
a. Attend a seminar to further gain knowledge in the process and management of sanitary landfill facility;
b. Conform with the pertinent provisions of RA 9003 on the maintenance of SLF and transportation equipment;
c. Construct temporary storage for the recyclable materials deposited in the disposal area of the SL; the sanitary landfill.
d. Transfer the residual wastes mistakenly dumped in the leachate pool to the disposal area and cover the same with soil;
e. Provide the needed facilities of the Rural Health Unit and Barangay Health Stations, such as concrete vaults and proper waste bins;
f. Install security fence around the septic/concrete vault with the required marking: “CAUTION: HAZARDOUS WASTE OR SHARPS DISPOSAL AREA- UNATHORIZED PERSONS KEEP OUT”; and
g. Regularly inspect, monitor and maintain the cleanliness inside and outside the premises of health facilities.
